               <head>Defensor, Liber scintillarum; Germany, 13th century, fourth quarter</head>
               <msContents>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="MS_Laud_Misc_631-item1">
                     <locus>(fols. 1r-32v)</locus>
                     <author key="person_281346627">Defensor</author>
                     <title key="work_1376">Liber scintillarum</title>
                     <note>(part)</note>
                     <rubric>Incipit liber Scintillarum de diversis voluminibus. In primis de carita<ex>te</ex>. </rubric>
                     <incipit>Dominus dicit in ewangelio. Maiorem caritatem nemo habet quam ut animam suam ponat quis pro amicis suis. </incipit>
                     <explicit> gaudeat quod talem habuerit </explicit>
                     <note>Fifty-four chapters, differing in order from the printed editions; ending with De filiis (c. 56/57) (PL 88.687–8), followed by an additional sentence: 'Triplex est filius, Filius Dei, filius hominis, filius diaboli. Filius Dei est qui semper bona agit aque reddit bonum de malo; filius hominis est, qui bonum reddit pro bono, malum pro malo; filius diaboli est qui semper mala agit, que malum reddit pro bono.' </note>
                     <note>Another hand has added a chapter list with folio references; same hand has added folio numbers in Roman numerals. </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="la">Latin</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
